dismissalText.commentary: Mohammad Yousuf c †Boucher b Hall 21 (29b 3x4 0x6 54m) SR: 72.41

dismissalComment.html: Huge strike for South Africa. Pakistan lose their best batsman. Teasing line outside off and Yousuf tries to guide it through vacant slip region, ends up steering it straight to Boucher. Pakistan in a hole here and that hole is constantly getting deeper.

headshotImage.caption: Imran Nazir player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Imran Nazir player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalComment.html: Gone! Pollock locks Nazir with a nip-backer and produces a edge. Lands on a length, outside the off stump and it jagged back in. Nazir drove at it loosely, didn't expect it would come back so much and ended up driving outside the line. Gets an inside-edge and it flew to left of Boucher who pouches it safely. Pretty smart catch. First blow to South Africa. Remember they won the toss and put Pakistan to bat under slightly overcast conditions.

headshotImage.caption: Younis Khan headshot
headshotImage.longCaption: Younis Khan headshot

dismissalComment.html: Pakistan slip deeper into crisis. Now Younis perishes. Fuller and around off stump line, Younis lunges forward - rather is sucked forward by the length, and drives, his bat well ahead of the body, gets a edge and is swallowed in the slips. Abdul Baseer would have just shrugged his shoulder!

dismissalText.commentary: Kamran Akmal run out (Gibbs) 3 (23b 0x4 0x6 30m) SR: 13.04

dismissalComment.html: Akmal's dismal time continues. He slips in the middle of the pitch and can't get back. Younis pushes a length delivery towards cover and Akmal rushes across like a express train. Younis is no mood to catch the train, he stays rooted to his station and Akmal has to turn back. He does but slips and falls. Gets up but by the time Gibbs had swooped in on the ball, sees that Akmal is just trying to get on his feet, and so runs with the ball towards the non-strikers end. And when he gets near, he underarms a direct hit and Akmal is well short of the crease.

commentTextItems.html: Crash! That booming slap slog does it. South Africa romp home to a 10-wicket win. Smith backed away to leg side and swung a length-delivery over the on side ring. Awesome strike to bring up the win. Both the batsmen had a party out there, none of the Pakistan players were invited to it. Balls disappeared over mid-on, mid-off, midwicket and where not as they bludgeoned 13 fours and 3 sixes.

commentPostTextItems.html: So South Africa have clinched a facile win and go up 2-1 in the five-match series. One more game left, can Pakistan come back to level the series. They have the talent, can they get it all together? This is Sriram Veera, signing off. Join George Binoy for the last game of the series. Good bye and good luck.

commentTextItems.html: Now de Villiers reaches his fifty with a dab. Both are having a party out there.
50 up for Smith in no time. shuffles across slightly, opens the bat-face and runs it down to thirdman
Violence! He backs away to the legside - doesn't charge down, and clubs a full-length delivery over mid-off.
fuller, hint of swing in, driven to left of mid on for a single. Now Smith on strike. Will he charge down the track again?
Murder! Flat-batted heave over long leg. Just leans forward, fetches a full-delivery from outside off and swings it over leg side. South Africa are looting runs here. Daylight robbery!

commentTextItems.html: cut away! turns in slightly from outside off stump, bit of width there and he carves it past backward point

dropped by Asif! What's more he gives away an extra run. It was short of length, on middle stump line, de Villiers backs away to pull but gets too much under the ball and it heads towards cow corner. Asif runs from mid-on, reaches it but clangs it. And then he doesn't react quickly and they rush across for another run
this time he walks across the stumps so that he can work with the turn and flicks it to behind square leg
some turn there. Breaks in from outside off, Smith shapes to cut and then is cramped by the extra turn and pushes it out to point
from round the stumps, drifts one on to the pads as he attempts a arm-ball, glanced away for a single
Carved away! Another charge, another boundary. He dances down the track and smokes a short of length delivery to widish long on.

commentTextItems.html: Slap! Smith rings the room service and Mahmood serves one short and wide, thrashed past point
slower one - from the back of the hand, outside off, tapped towards gully and they will get a easy single
pleasing drive to mid-off. Full in length and outside off, he presents the full face of the blade to it.
overpitched on the off stump line, down comes the bat straight, meets the ball flush in the middle and sends the ball back to the bowler
pushed through a bit, outside off stump, doesn't turn back in and Smith is beaten going for a cut

dismissalText.commentary: Kamran Akmal run out (Gibbs) 3 (23b 0x4 0x6 30m) SR: 13.04

dismissalComment.html: Akmal's dismal time continues. He slips in the middle of the pitch and can't get back. Younis pushes a length delivery towards cover and Akmal rushes across like a express train. Younis is no mood to catch the train, he stays rooted to his station and Akmal has to turn back. He does but slips and falls. Gets up but by the time Gibbs had swooped in on the ball, sees that Akmal is just trying to get on his feet, and so runs with the ball towards the non-strikers end. And when he gets near, he underarms a direct hit and Akmal is well short of the crease.

stories.title: 'One of the best bowling performances I've seen' - Smith
stories.subTitle: South Africa vs Pakistan, 4th ODI, Cape Town
stories.summary: Graeme Smith, the South African captain, heaped praise on his bowlers for decimating Pakistan and setting up a ten-wicket win at Cape Town

stories.title: Seamers set up crushing win
stories.subTitle: South Africa vs Pakistan, 4th ODI, Cape Town
stories.summary: Shaun Pollock, supported by an assembly line of bristling seamers, set Pakistan up for the kill, before South Africa's openers finished it with a lack of mercy that Jack the Ripper would've shivered at

stories.title: Winning momentum up for grabs
stories.subTitle: South Africa v Pakistan, 4th ODI, Cape Town
stories.summary: Unless Pakistan can persuade the ICC to give them an extension on naming their World Cup squad this will be the last time these two teams play with a chance of swaying opinions
